@hissst69 If you can find a way of attaching it, the popular online auction site lists a large number of rotary counters for a very reasonable price.
I would advise against trying to use a bench grinder under power for winding coils. It's designed to go fast and to take a long time to slow down. That leads to some safety concerns. If I wanted to build a coil winder I would be looking at an old cordless drill and a foot switch.
As it is, I'm very fortunate to own a purpose built coil winder.
